<strong>using syndication feeds to post</strong><br>
<p>If you have a syndication feed available on your site, you can use it to create a post on Austin Stories.</p>

<p><a href="/index.php/members/site/browse/"{if $popup_flag==true} class="popup"{/if}>Edit your site information</a>, and fill in the field <strong>URL for syndication feed</strong> is filled with the URL of your feed.</p>

<p>This function is powered by MagpieRSS, which supports RSS 1.0, RSS 2.0 and Atom 0.3. Your feed must conform to these specifications.</p>

<p>To post from your syndication feed:</p>

<ol>
<li> <p>Click on <strong>Add a post from RSS</strong> from the left-navigation menu.</p></li>

<li> <p>Click <strong>[Add]</strong> next to the entry title you wish to post to the site. If you have more than one site with a syndication feed, each of those feeds will be listed.</p>

<ol type="a">
<li> <p>If a post similar to the one in your syndication feed already exists on the site, you will be given the following options to handle it.</p>

<ul>
<li> <strong>[Edit]</strong> Edit the post already in the database.</li>
<li> <strong>[Replace]</strong> Edit the post already in the database with the chosen item from your syndication feed.</li>
<li> <strong>[Delete]</strong> Delete the existing post.</li>
</ul>

</li>
</ol>

</li>

